>tygra.Michigan.COM) asks:
>>>I'm planning to use DES in CBC mode as a Hash function, and I was
>>>thinking of just using all zeros as the key.  Is there any known
>>>weakness using a zero key with DES?
It is (IMHO) lot's easier to invert some DES-rounds, if the key is
zero. Try setting the data to zero, and use the key as hash-input...
(You might want to look at the implementation of the UNIX passwd-
crypt which also sets the data to zero, and uses the key for 'hashing' ;-)
the password)
Friendly greetings,
	Germano Caronni	
